          <code code="11506-3" codeSystem="2.16.840.1.113883.6.1" codeSystemName="LOINC" displayName="Progress Notes" />
          <title>PROGRESS NOTES</title>
          <text>
            <table xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema">
              <thead><tr><th>Date</th><th>Provider</th><th>Note Type</th><th>Note Text</th><th>Location</th></tr></thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr><td>03/18/2026</td><td>Cory Denton, FNP</td><td>Progress Note</td><td>CC: COPD follow-up, lung nodule surveillance, smoking cessation.
HPI: 66yo female with severe COPD (GOLD Stage III, FEV1 38%). On triple inhaler therapy + chronic azithromycin + home O2. Last exacerbation Jan 2026 (prednisone burst + augmentin). Lung nodule 8mm RUL found on LDCT screening Sept 2025 -- follow-up CT due now. Currently smoking 1/2 ppd -- down from 1 ppd. Started nicotine patch 14mg. Motivated to quit. Reports increased depression during exacerbation, stable now on sertraline.
Pulm Rehab: Completed 12-week program. Functional capacity improved. 6MWT: 200m (was 150m).
PE: Barrel chest. Lungs -- diffuse expiratory wheezes, prolonged expiration. No crackles. O2 92% on 2L. CV RRR. Cachexic.
Assessment:
# COPD severe (J44.1): FEV1 38%. Triple therapy + azithromycin prophylaxis. Pulm rehab complete.
# Lung nodule (R91.1): 8mm RUL. Follow-up CT chest ordered today per Lung-RADS guidelines.
# Smoking cessation (F17.210): Reduced to 1/2 ppd. Nicotine patch 14mg. Discussed adding bupropion -- patient amenable. Start 150mg daily x 3 days then BID.
# Respiratory failure (J96.11): Stable on 2L. ABG showed compensated respiratory acidosis.
# Osteoporosis (M81.0): On calcium/D. Consider bisphosphonate after dental clearance.
# Depression (F33.1): Stable on sertraline. PHQ-9 = 8.
Plan: CT chest ordered. Start bupropion for smoking cessation. Pulmonology 2 months. Return 6 weeks. Advance directive discussion -- patient open, will complete next visit.</td><td>Family Practice Associates of Chesterfield</td></tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </text>
        </section>
